fields.description: Handcrafted from 100% reclaimed teak and finished with a stunning mocha color. This contemporary 6-Drawer Dresser looks so put together with it's golden handles that standout like buttons on a navy coat.
We fell in love with the grain of the wood, the straight lines, and especially the feet on this dresser. Sustainable (with with reclaimed wood) and handcrafted, this is a one of a kind piece.

The warm and elegant grain of the Teak wood is a stand-out feature... and did we mention that it's made of 100% reclaimed wood and handcrafted! Designed with soft closing drawer tracks, it allows the wood to speak for itself. What's more we love the mid-century design of this 9 drawer piece.

Gorgeous mid-century side table made from 100% reclaimed wood and handcrafted! Each of the 3 drawers leverage soft closing technology, allowing the wood to speak for itself. The warm and elegant grain of the Teak wood is a stand-out feature.

We love the interesting look of this shingled, 6-drawer dresser. It's natural honey color finish is so sweet. Remember, no two pieces will be alike. This is handcrafted and made of 100% reclaimed teak.
We love the assymmetrical look of this 3-Drawer 1-Door End Table.  This piece is artisan crafted with meticulous care. Each piece has a different wood variation, which helps to make each item unique.

The reclaimed teak used in this piece was salvaged from a 100 year old home that was being demolished. It was reconstructed into this beautiful 2 level cocktail table. Handcrafted and with a natural honey color finish. Bring a piece of history home.
Modern, shingled credenza made from reclaimed teak. Has 2 touch door hinges and 3 drawers that incorporate soft closing technology. Handcrafted so every item is unique.
Mid-Century Modern media cabinet. It has three soft closing drawers, and two solid wood doors each with two shelves to ensure ample storage space. Made by hand, with 100% reclaimed teak.

It's as cool as James Dean. We're convinced that's how this coffee table got its name. Unique shape. Handcrafted (of course). Made from 100% reclaimed wood. You really can't get any better than that. No 2 pieces are alike.

Grounded, conveying the strength of a rooted tree. We like the stature of this coffee table. It tends to draw the eye. What's more appealing is that it is made out of 100% reclaimed wood -- yes, eco-friendly, sustainable, all of that good stuff. It's also hand made so that no two pieces are exactly alike.

Artisan crafted with meticulous care. Given its handmade and hand-finished nature, variations in the wood is to be expected and celebrated. The reclaimed Teak used in this piece is approximately 100 years old, and was salvaged from a house being demolished.

Each item is unique and no two are exactly alike

Fans available for an additional $100 each (up to 2)

The reclaimed Teak used in this piece is approximately 100 years old, and was salvaged from a house being demolished. The reclaimed steel used was salvaged from a 1940′s ship. This side table has a natural honey color finish complimented with gold colored base. We love it's unique architecture. This piece is handcrafted.

There's something gorgeous about the simplicity of this table. We love the splayed legs at the bottom and how they come strongly together in the middle (what sturdy construction). Made from 100 year old teak, which was reclaimed. Handcrafted.
Nice and simple, mid-century modern dining table. It has gorgeous splayed legs and a beautiful teak grain. Handcrafted and made from reclaimed wood.
We liked these teak dining table chairs because of the intricate panelling on the seat. Sustainable (100% reclaimed teak) and modern, these are a great pick.

A nice, simple dining chair. We like the 2 slats in the back contrasted with the full slab of teak for the seat. Nicely constructed -- handmade in fact. Also, did we mention that the teak is reclaimed? So, you're sure to get a one of a kind piece every time.
circa: 1860

A perfect fit  for your precious book collection. There are some things that look good just because of their appeal and this Japanese Antique Tansu Furniture has got that appeal. From the Kyoto region of Japan (crica 1920) this piece is made of Hinoki wood that adds the sense of typical Japanese culture while not distracting the existing environment around.  It comes int 2 sections.

circa: 1900
region: shiga
Mid-century rocker in very good shape expect for tear in back.  Great bones - recline in style and history.
Beautiful vintage Turkish sitting stool with original leather seat cushion cover.  Why crouch when you can sit in style?!
We don't run across too many Art Deco pieces these days so this one really stands out.   Great detail and in good shape.  A little wear on the top.
1930s era office chair.  Original leather seat cushion still in good condition.
Solid Mahogany Dresser with File Drawers
